{"id": "duc04-testb-49:14#42", "contents": "Secretary of State Madeleine Albright expressed disappointment with the economic confusion within the new Russian government of Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov, warning Russia about the dangers of an anti-Western policy. In her comprehensive review of U.S.-Russian relations, Albright stated that Washington is \"deeply concerned\" about Russia's direction and does not expect the crisis to soon abate. She criticized the Russian government's proposed economic measures, such as printing new money and imposing price and capital controls, suggesting that some members of Primakov's team lack understanding of the global economy."}
